		<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
			
			<p>@Chris,  that&#8217;s my guess.  I&#8217;m assuming the surveyor did not have an accurate yardstick to measure the 16 feet.  So he couldn&#8217;t just measure that and divide by 16.  (If he had an accurate measure then this whole procedure would have been unnecessary).</p>
<p>But if measured off with a rope or a line in the dirt, he could divide by 16 by repeated folding and cutting of a rope, or repeated bisection with a compass and straightedge.</p>
		</div>

